dical attention if they occur, including edema, shortness of breath, coughing, hematuria, and decreased urination.', 'Excretion', 'Caution is advised when inotersen is prescribed with nephrotoxic drugs and other drugs that may impair renal function (e.', 'Major', 'pharmacodynamic', NULL, 'https://ddinter2.scbdd.com/server/interact/8368/', '', 'Lamivudine, Paritaprevir, Glecaprevir, Maraviroc, Amprenavir, Simeprevir, Zanamivir, Cabotegravir, Lenacapavir, Telaprevir, Velpatasvir, More', 'Dextromethorphan, Valbenazine, Dalfampridine, Sodium oxybate, Riluzole, Tetrabenazine, Pitolisant, Amifampridine, Deutetrabenazine, Tafamidis', 1767369485);
